Herein, a series of coumarin-benzo [b]thiophene 1, 1-dioxide hybrids were designed, synthesized and biologically evaluated as STAT3 mitochondria-targeting inhibitors (Fig. 1
                     ), triggering dual suppression of STAT3 phosphorylation on Tyr705 and Ser727. To the best of our knowledge, no fluorescent dual STAT3 phosphorylation inhibitors have been reported [29,30,34,44–51]. These hybrids were discovered to accumulate in mitochondria, cause Δψ
                     m depolarization, increase intracellular ROS and further induce apoptosis and necrosis. These new inhibitors might be promising candidates for cancer therapy.
